## Conclusion
This experiment demonstrates how distance-based learning methods can be applied to image analysis tasks. By combining face detection with feature extraction and clustering, it is possible to group visually similar data points without labelled training data. The results highlight the effectiveness of K-Means clustering when meaningful features such as hue and saturation are used.
